ing%20system%2C%20industry%20bodies%20that%20represent%20Ukrainian%20defense%20companies%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20Artillery%20systems%20remain%20critical%20in%20this%20war.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20much%20of%20this%20conflict%2C%20Western%20partners%20have%20sent%20their%20weapons%20to%20Ukraine%2C%20emptying%20stockpiles.%20This%20new%20model%20involves%20partners%20purchasing%20weapons%20for%20Kyiv's%20forces%20directly%20from%20Ukrainian%20manufacturers.%20The%20former%20approach%20is%20still%20key%20for%20Ukraine%2C%20but%20the%20latter%20has%20shown%20real%20potential.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20system%2C%20pioneered%20by%20NATO%20member%20Denmark%20and%20nicknamed%20the%20Danish%20Model%2C%20has%20helped%20Ukraine%20get%20more%20weapons%20for%20it%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-did-russia-invade-ukraine-putin-politics-motive-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Efight%20back%20against%20Russia's%20invasion.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20particular%2C%20it%20has%20had%20a%20really%20%26quot%3Bsignificant%20impact%26quot%3B%20on%20Bohdana%20production%2C%20Serhiy%20Goncharov%2C%20the%20CEO%20of%20the%20National%20Association%20of%20Ukrainian%20Defense%20Industries%20(NAUDI)%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20His%20group%20represents%20around%20100%20Ukrainian%20companies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20large%2C%20green-coloured%20weapon%20inside%20a%20trench%20topped%20with%20a%20canopy%20with%20a%20man%20in%20camouflage%20gear%20standing%20beside%20it%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F687f8297f748d8c055f6050a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20Ukrainian%20soldier%20operates%20a%202S22%20Bohdana.%3Cp%3EDmytro%20Smolienko%2FUkrinform%2FNurPhoto%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EProduction%20increased%20from%20six%20units%20a%20month%20in%202023%20to%20more%20than%2020%20of%20these%20systems%20in%202025%2C%20according%20to%20Ukraine's%20Defence%20Procurement%20Agency.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Bohdana%20is%20a%20NATO-standard%2C%20self-propelled%20howitzer%20produced%20by%20Ukraine's%20Kramatorsk%20Heavy%20Duty%20Machine%20Tool%20Building%20Plant%2C%20and%20Goncharov%20described%20it%20as%20%26quot%3Ba%20symbol%20of%20resistance%20and%20the%20symbol%20of%20Ukrainian%20industry.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFunding%20weapons%20that%20are%20made%20in%20Ukraine%20is%20important%20given%20current%20challenges.%20European%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-veteran-in-ukraine-says-ammo-desperately-needed-not-tanks-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Emilitary%20stockpiles%20have%20little%20to%20spare%20for%20Ukraine%2C%20and%20%3C%2Fa%3Emany%20Western%20defense%20companies%20already%20have%20big%20backlogs%20in%20production.%20So%20even%20funding%20new%20Western%20weapons%20doesn't%20help%20Ukraine%20in%20the%20short%20term.%20Ukraine%20frequently%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-weakening-ukraine-position-negoatiations-part-of-a-pattern-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Edeals%20with%20shortages%20of%20foreign%20weapons%20from%20its%20partners%3C%2Fa%3E%20given%20the%20war's%20tremendous%20demand%20for%20war%20material.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20model%20is%20also%20useful%20for%20NATO%2C%20with%20many%20countries%20in%20the%20alliance%20wanting%20to%20maintain%20and%20grow%20their%20own%20arsenals%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-better-positioned-attack-europe-before-ukraine-war-nato-lithuania-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eworried%20that%20Russian%20aggression%20could%20someday%20extend%20beyond%20Ukraine%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGoncharov%20said%20that%20the%20Danish%20model%20has%20helped%20Ukrainian%20industry%20scale%20production%20by%20giving%20it%20the%20finance%20it%20needs%2C%20as%20usually%20it%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-defense-industry-can-make-more-weapons-extra-capacity-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Elimited%20to%20what%20Ukraine's%20defense%20ministry%20can%20afford%2C%20which%20is%20out%20of%20sync%20with%20industrial%20capacity%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20financial%20support%2C%20he%20said%2C%20gives%20producers%20%26quot%3Bmore%20confidence%26quot%3B%20to%20increase%20their%20production%2C%20knowing%20the%20funding%20is%20there.%20In%20addition%20to%20the%20homemade%20howitzers%2C%20the%20Danish%20model%20has%20helped%20fund%20more%20drones%2C%20as%20well%20as%20anti-tank%20and%20anti-ship%20missile%20systems.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20host%20of%20countries%2C%20like%20Sweden%20and%20Iceland%2C%20are%20giving%20money%20to%20Ukraine%20through%20the%20model%2C%20which%20is%20growing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202024%2C%20the%20model%20finalized%20procurements%20for%20weaponry%20worth%20more%20than%20%24550%20million%2C%20and%20Ukrainian%20Defence%20Minister%20Rustem%20Umerov%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmod.gov.ua%2Fen%2Fnews%2Fukraine-to-receive-1-3-billion-under-the-danish-model-in-2025%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20last%20month%20that%20support%20through%20this%20model%20is%20expected%20to%20reach%20more%20than%20%241.7%20billion%20this%20year.%20And%20more%20partner%20countries%20are%20continuing%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmilitarnyi.com%2Fen%2Fnews%2Fcanada-will-allocate-28-million-for-weapons-production-under-the-danish-model%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ejoin%3C%2Fa%3E%20while%20some%20countries%2C%20like%20Germany%2C%20are%20launching%20independent%20programs%20inspired%20by%20the%20model.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%220d2d4c28-5e6a-4cb0-af86-0dd77dabdcce%5C%22%3ENew%20help%20for%20Ukraine%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETroels%20Lund%20Poulsen%2C%20Denmark's%20defense%20minister%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20in%20March%20that%20the%20model%20so%20far%20%26quot%3Bhas%20been%20a%20great%20success%26quot%3B%20and%20that%20under%20it%2C%20the%20weapon%20prices%20are%20%26quot%3Bquite%20low%20compared%20to%20buying%20the%20artillery%20systems%20in%20Europe.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGoncharov%20called%20the%20model%20a%20%26quot%3Bnew%20vision%20of%20how%20you%20can%20support%20Ukraine%26quot%3B%20and%20said%20that%20work%20on%20the%20Bohdana%20was%20a%20big%20%26quot%3Bsuccess%20story.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Large%20artillery%20shells%20lean%20on%20the%20side%20of%20a%20trench%20with%20a%20figure%20in%20camouflage%20gear%20and%20a%20helmet%20squatting%20behind%20them%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F687f835d3d5881a51c1dbd40%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20soldier%20squats%20by%20155mm%20shells%20for%20a%202S22%20Bohdana%20self-propelled%20howitzer.%3Cp%3EDmytro%20Smolienko%2FUkrinform%2FNurPhoto%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20NAUDI%20has%20a%20list%20of%20weapons%20that%20it%20is%20ready%20to%20make%20more%20of%20through%20the%20Danish%20model%20or%20a%20similar%20model%2C%20including%20artillery%2C%20armored%20vehicles%2C%20jamming%20systems%2C%20and%20drones.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIhor%20Fedirko%2C%20the%20CEO%20of%20the%20Ukrainian%20Council%20of%20Defence%20Industry%20(UCDI)%2C%20a%20body%20that%20represents%20more%20than%20100%20companies%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20the%20increase%20in%20Bohdana%20production%20was%20%26quot%3Bmade%20possible%20thanks%20to%20the%20Danish%20model%20and%20associated%20funding.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20the%20capacity%20exists%20for%20increased%20total%20production%2C%20he%20said.%20Fedirko%20described%20the%20Danish%20model%20as%20%26quot%3Bthe%20largest%20hope%20for%20the%20private%20sector%26quot%3B%20in%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWithin%20Ukraine's%20defense%20industry%2C%20%26quot%3Bther