mmer%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.americanimmigrationcouncil.org%2Fblog%2Fgraduation-ice-targets-young-dreamers%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereports%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20Immigration%20and%20Customs%20Enforcement%20has%20arrested%20young%20people%20brought%20to%20the%20US%20by%20their%20parents%20as%20children%20as%20they%20go%20about%20their%20day%2C%20going%20to%20school%20or%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20so%20frustrating.%20I%20came%20here%20at%204%2C%20so%20I've%20lived%20here%20my%20whole%20entire%20life%2C%26quot%3B%20Hernandez%20said.%20%26quot%3BI'm%20from%20Mexico%2C%20but%20I%20don't%20know%20anything%20about%20the%20country.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMillions%20of%20young%20immigrants%20raised%20and%20educated%20in%20the%20US%20are%20entering%20adulthood%20ready%20to%20contribute%20to%20the%20economy.%20Business%20Insider%20spoke%20to%20Gen%20Z%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fimmigrationforum.org%2Farticle%2Ffact-sheet-on-deferred-action-for-childhood-arrivals-daca%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThere%2520are%2520as%2520many%2520as%25203.6%2520million%2Cparticipation%252C%2520only%2520about%2520800%252C000%2520Dreamers%2520were%2520protected.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDreamers%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20who%20came%20to%20the%20US%20as%20children%20and%20now%20say%20they%20are%20stuck%2C%20unable%20to%20fully%20realize%20their%20American%20dream.%20As%20immigration%20enforcement%20rises%2C%20these%20undocumented%20young%20adults%20face%20an%20uncertain%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20want%20a%20career%2C%26quot%3B%20Hernandez%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20can't%20be%20a%20barista%20forever.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f60fb6db-7687-4a0e-9d4b-bd1263171fee%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E'Keep%20working%2C%20keep%20following%20the%20rules%2C%20and%20eventually%20our%20time%20will%20come'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EJuan%20Robles%2C%2028%2C%20has%20work%20authorization%20through%20DACA%2C%20or%20Deferred%20Action%20for%20Childhood%20Arrivals%2C%20an%20Obama-era%20program%20that%20is%20now%20caught%20up%20in%20a%20legal%20battle%20that%20paused%20new%20applications.%20Every%20two%20years%2C%20Robles%20has%20to%20reapply%20to%20maintain%20his%20status.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20consider%20myself%20American%20just%20as%20much%20as%20any%20other%20person%2C%20and%20I%20think%20I've%20done%20a%20lot%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Robles%2C%20who%20came%20to%20the%20US%20at%20age%207%20in%202004.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20journey%20toward%20building%20his%20American%20dream%20hasn't%20been%20easy.%20He%20worked%20to%20put%20himself%20through%20college%20because%20he%20wasn't%20eligible%20for%20loans%20or%20state%20grants.%20The%20first%20time%20he%20tried%20to%20buy%20a%20home%2C%20DACA%20recipients%20weren't%20eligible%20for%20FHA%20financing.%20%3Cstrong%3EHe%20isn't%20eligible%20to%20receive%20any%20Social%20Security%20benefits%20when%20he%20retires.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20was%20like%20a%20slap%20in%20the%20face%2C%26quot%3B%20Robles%20said%20of%20the%20barriers.%20%26quot%3BNot%20only%20did%20we%20have%20to%20work%20hard%20for%20what%20we%20have%2C%20but%20we%20have%20to%20work%20a%20lot%20harder%20just%20because%20of%20who%20we%20are.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202022%2C%20he%20cashed%20out%20his%20retirement%20savings%20and%20borrowed%20%2420%2C000%20from%20his%20parents%20to%20jump-start%20his%20business%2C%20Juanderful%20Tacos.%20He%20said%20business%20has%20been%20booming%20and%20last%20year%2C%20he%20owed%20the%20IRS%20%248%2C759%20in%20taxes%20from%20sales.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20have%20the%20audacity%20to%20say%20that%20immigrants%20don't%20pay%20taxes%2C%26quot%3B%20Robles%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20hoped%20his%20professional%20efforts%20and%20lack%20of%20criminal%20record%20would%20prove%20that%20he%20deserves%20to%20earn%20citizenship.%20With%20the%20recent%20escalation%20in%20ICE%20arrests%2C%20he%20feels%20a%20renewed%20sense%20of%20despair.%20More%20than%20a%20decade%20since%20DACA%20was%20established%2C%20Robles%2C%20who%20lives%20in%20Phoenix%2C%20is%20facing%20the%20risk%20of%20deportation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20are%20present%20in%20the%20United%20States%20illegally%2C%20you%20will%20be%20deported%2C%26quot%3B%20Abigail%20Jackson%2C%20a%20spokesperson%20for%20the%20White%20House%2C%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fla-immigrant-street-vendors-work-through-ice-raids-protests-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3Epreviously%20told%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cstrong%3E%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20the%20promise%20President%20Trump%20made%20to%20the%20American%20people%20that%20the%20administration%20is%20committed%20to%20keeping%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERobles%20and%20his%20wife%2C%20who%20is%20also%20undocumented%2C%20have%20been%20outspoken%20about%20their%20status%20online%20and%20are%20longtime%20immigrant%20activists.%20The%20bio%20on%20their%20restaurant's%20Instagram%20page%20reads%2C%20%26quot%3Bvery%20proudly%20DACA-owned%20and%20operated.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20got%20to%20just%20keep%20our%20heads%20down%2C%20keep%20working%2C%20keep%20following%20the%20rules%2C%20and%20eventually%20our%20time%20will%20come%2C%26quot%3B%20Robles%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20really%20can't%20hope%20for%20anything%20else.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%224491802b-63d8-44ce-be5e-596b3233889f%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E'What%20now%3F%20I%20still%20can't%20get%20a%20job.'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20many%20in%20the%20US%2C%20a%20college%20degree%20is%20an%20important%20stepping%20stone%20toward%20the%20middle%20class.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ssa.gov%2Fpolicy%2Fdocs%2Fresearch-summaries%2Feducation-earnings.html%23%3A~%3Atext%3DMen%2520with%2520bachelor%2527s%2520degrees%2520earn%2Cmen%2520and%2520%24310%252C000%2520for%2520women.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAccording%20to%20the%20Social%20Security%20Administration%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20those%20with%20higher%20education%20degrees%20earn%20over%20%241%20million%20more%20in%20median%20lifetime%20earnings%20than%20their%20peers%20without%20a%20degree.%20But%20a%20professional%20career%20is%20a%20much%20harder%20step%20for%20young%20people%20living%20in%20the%20US%20on%20DACA%20status%20or%20without%20permanent%20legal%20status.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20undocumented%20LA-based%20Gen%20Zer%20said%20she%20dropped%20out%20of%20Art%20Center%20College%20of%20Design%20because%20she%20maxed%20out%20on%20the%20financial%20aid%20and%20loans%20the%20state%20of%20California%20offers%20to%20non-citizen%20residents%20and%20didn't%20qualify%20for%20federal%20aid%20because%20she%20isn't%20a%20refugee%20or%20permanent%20resident.%20She's%20been%20afraid%20to%20continue%20her%20work%20as%20a%20freelance%20photographer%20due%20to%20recent%20ICE%20raids%20in%20Los%20Angeles%2C%20and%20has%20turned%20down%20job%20opportunities%2C%20which%20leaves%20her%20worried%20about%20paying%20rent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJennifer%20R.%20N%C3%A1jera%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20Ethnic%20Studies%20at%20the%20University%20of%20California%2C%20Riverside%2C%20said%20that%20in%20addition%20to%20the%20professional%20and%20financial%20strain%2C%20students%20without%20legal%20status%20are%20physically%20and%20emotionally%20affected%20by%20the%20threat%20of%20deportation%20and%20family%20separation.%20Statewide%20surveys%20at%20California's%20public%20universities%20found%20that%2028%25%20of%20undocumented%20students%20and%2030%25%20of%20students%20with%20undocumented%20parents%20had%20reported%20clinical%20depressive%20symptoms%20compared%20to%2021%25%20of%20their%20peers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20a%20lot%20of%20disillusion%20with%20the%20American%20dream%20among%20immigrant%20communities%2C%20especially%20working-class%20immigrant%20communities%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20N%C3%A1jera%2C%20who%20works%20with%20and%20studies%20undocumented%20student%20activists.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHernandez%20can%20relate.%20She%20graduated%20with%20a%20bachelor's%20in%20health%20science%20from%20Sacramento%20State%20University%20in%202023%2C%20but%20finding%20work%20in%20her%20field%20of%20study%20has%20been%20harder.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20hoped%20to%20receive%20US%20citizenship%20when%20she%20married%20her%20high%20school%20boyfriend%20in%202024.%20When%20the%20marriage%20broke%20up%20last%20year%2C%20she%20was%20on%20the%20cusp%20of%20securing%20a%20green%20card.%20She%20is%20now%20on%20a%20different%20pathway%20to%20citizenship%20through%20the%20Violence%20Against%20Women%20Act.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHernandez%20feels%20frustrated%20that%20she's%20back%20to%20living%20with%20her%20parents%20and%20working%20an%20hourly%20wage%20service%20job.%20She%20wants%20more%20for%20her%20life%2C%20and%20is%20attending%20a%20community%20college%20to%20become%20a%20nurse%20because%20immigration%20status%20is%20not%20a%20barrier%20to%20getting%20a%20license%20in%20California.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGetting%20hired%20at%20a%20hospital%20is%20a%20different%20story%3A%20She%20would%20need%20to%20have%20US%20citizenship%20or%20a%20green%20card.%20She%20knows%20it's%20a%20risk%20to%20take%20on%20additional%20debt%20for%20nursing%20school%20when%20she%20might%20not%20get%20hired%20until%20a%20multi-year%20legalization%20process%20is%20over.%20Hernandez%20said%20it's%20worth%20it%20to%20keep%20driving%20toward%20her%20goal%20of%20making%20it%20beyond%20minimum-wage%20jobs%20that%20don't%20provide%20benefits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20got%20my%20EMT%2C%20I%20got%20my%20degree%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Hernandez%2C%20who%20doesn't%20qualify%20for%20a%20paramedic%20license%20in%20California%20because%20of%20her%20legal%20status.%20%26quot%3BWhat%20now%3F%20I%20still%20can't%20get%20a%20job.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.busin