-toc-id%3D%5C%22d9d6f730-3299-463e-8186-7b4ba64b5e7d%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EOzempic%20is%20hitting%20eating%20disorder%20centers%20hard%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAbout%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.kff.org%2Fhealth-costs%2Fpoll-finding%2Fkff-health-tracking-poll-may-2024-the-publics-use-and-views-of-glp-1-drugs%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eone%20in%20eight%3C%2Fa%3E%20adults%20is%20currently%20taking%20a%20GLP-1%2C%20such%20as%20Ozempic%20and%20Mounjaro%2C%20designed%20for%20diabetes%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feli-lilly-zepbound-ozempic-wegovy-novo-nordisk-weight-loss-drugs-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EZepbound%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fquit-wegovy-ozempic-no-evidence-stop-taking-works-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EWegovy%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20marketed%20for%20weight%20loss.%20The%20medications%20work%20by%20mimicking%20GLP-1%2C%20a%20natural%20hormone%20that%20helps%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhabits-for-healthy-blood-sugar-levels-doctor-advice-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eregulate%20blood%20sugar%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20delay%20digestion%2C%20and%20signal%20fullness%20to%20the%20brain.%20While%20originally%20intended%20for%20people%20with%20type%202%20diabetes%20or%20chronic%20obesity%2C%20these%20drugs%20have%20been%20co-opted%20by%20those%20seeking%20weight%20loss%20%E2%80%94%20even%20if%20it's%20not%20medically%20necessary.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EExperts%20warn%20that%20these%20medications%20can%20trigger%20new%20eating%20disorders%2C%20worsen%20existing%20ones%2C%20and%20complicate%20recovery.%20Brittany%20Lacour%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Enational%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Edirector%20of%20clinical%20assessment%20intake%20at%20Eating%20Recovery%20Centers%2C%20with%20programs%20across%20the%20country%2C%20said%20the%20number%20of%20people%20who%20have%20come%20into%20ERC%20already%20on%20a%20GLP-1%20went%20from%2011%20in%202023%20to%2031%20in%202024.%20So%20far%20there%20have%20been%2014%20cases%20in%202025%2C%20including%20a%2014-year-old%20child.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%227548%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Elizabeth%20Wassenaar%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68810fe3f748d8c055f6236a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225034%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDr.%20Elizabeth%20Wassenaar%2C%20regional%20medical%20director%20of%20Eating%20Recovery%20Center%20of%20the%20West%2C%20says%20more%20and%20more%20people%20with%20GLP-1%20prescriptions%20are%20being%20admitted%20with%20eating%20disorders.%3Cp%3EMichael%20Ciaglo%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20are%20seeing%20people%20who%20are%20coming%20into%20treatment%20with%20a%20relapse%20or%20new%20onset%2C%20and%20most%20of%20them%20are%20presenting%20with%20restrictive%20eating%20patterns%2C%20like%20anorexia%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Dr.%20Elizabeth%20Wassenaar%2C%20regional%20medical%20director%20of%20Eating%20Recovery%20Center%20of%20the%20West.%20She%20is%20also%20seeing%20an%20increase%20in%20atypical%20anorexia%2C%20a%20form%20of%20anorexia%20nervosa%20where%20someone%20is%20significantly%20restricting%20calories%20but%20is%20of%20average%20or%20above%20average%20weight.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDr.%20Joel%20Jahraus%2C%20vice%20president%20of%20medical%20services%20at%20Monte%20Nido%2C%20a%20national%20eating%20disorder%20treatment%20provider%2C%20has%20seen%20a%2025%25%20to%2033%25%20increase%20in%20patients%20already%20on%20GLP-1%20medications%20when%20they%20enter%20treatment.%20Most%2C%20if%20not%20all%2C%20of%20them%20have%20a%20binge-eating%20disorder.%20%26quot%3BA%20year%20ago%20there%20was%20no%20one%20presenting%20for%20an%20intake%20on%20a%20GLP-1%20and%20then%20it%20increased%20to%20a%20couple%20a%20month%20going%20back%206%20months%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20These%20days%2C%20Monte%20Nido%20gets%20around%20three%20to%20five%20patients%20a%20month%20who%20are%20on%20a%20GLP-1.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%2C%20he%20notes%2C%20patients%20often%20hide%20their%20GLP-1%20use%20from%20the%20person%20doing%20the%20intake%2C%20typically%20only%20bringing%20it%20up%20when%20they%20show%20up%20onsite%20for%20actual%20admission.%20Doctors%20attribute%20their%20reticence%20to%20shame%2C%20embarrassment%2C%20and%20the%20fear%20that%20their%20medications%20might%20be%20taken%20away%20from%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20effect%20of%20these%20meds%20can%20go%20absolutely%20contrary%20to%20the%20goals%20of%20eating%20disorder%20treatment%2C%20so%20it's%20important%20to%20figure%20that%20out%2C%26quot%3B%20Jahraus%20said.%20%26quot%3BIf%20they%20are%20low%20body%20weight%20and%20have%20no%20other%20indication%20for%20use%20such%20as%20diabetes%20or%20cardiovascular%20disease%2C%20there%20is%20no%20place%20for%20the%20GLP-1%20meds%20because%20the%20medication%20causes%20further%20weight%20loss.%20If%20they%20are%20normal%20or%20above%20normal%20body%20weight%2C%20we%20go%20through%20a%20process%20to%20gauge%20if%20they'll%20be%20successful%20at%20stopping%20their%20eating%20disorders%2C%20but%20that%20comes%20after%20treatment%20is%20initiated.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%224f038bc3-7d87-4c0f-b882-453715290178%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E'I'm%20not%20taking%20it%20for%20the%20right%20reasons%2C%20but%20I%20feel%20that%20I%20need%20to'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20two%20decades%2C%20Rose%2C%2032%2C%20who%20lives%20outside%20Boise%2C%20Idaho%2C%20wrestled%20with%20restrictive%20eating%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fglennon-doyle-describes-identity-shift-from-anorexia-nervosa-diagnosis-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ebulimia%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20cycling%20in%20and%20out%20of%20residential%20and%20non-residential%20treatment%20programs.%20Anything%20that%20would%20help%20her%20shed%20the%20100%20pounds%20she%20gained%20when%20pregnant%20with%20her%20son%20and%20quiet%20the%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fweight-loss-glp-1-drugs-ozempic-wegovy-mounjaro-effects-future-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Efood%20noise%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20the%20obsessive%20thoughts%20about%20meals%2C%20calories%2C%20exercise%2C%20and%20weight%20that%20relentlessly%20plagued%20her%20%E2%80%94%20was%20enticing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20when%20she%20was%20diagnosed%20with%20diabetes%20three%20years%20ago%2C%20she%20finally%20had%20a%20%26quot%3Blegit%26quot%3B%20medical%20reason%20to%20ask%20her%20internist%20for%20a%20prescription%20for%20Ozempic.%20She%20was%20elated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHer%20endocrinologist%2C%20dietician%2C%20and%20therapist%20were%20not.%20For%20people%20like%20Rose%2C%20with%20a%20history%20of%20restrictive%20eating%2C%20the%20inability%20to%20be%20in%20tune%20with%20their%20body%20could%20be%20disastrous.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20Rose%20managed%20to%20persuade%20her%20internist%20to%20give%20her%20a%20prescription.%20He%20nervously%20agreed%2C%20but%20with%20strict%20conditions%3A%20she%20had%20to%20eat%20at%20least%201%2C500%20calories%20a%20day%2C%20not%20exercise%20compulsively%2C%20and%20not%20lose%20more%20than%20two%20pounds%20a%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20long%20as%20I%20was%20meeting%20those%20goals%20and%20all%20else%20was%20OK%2C%20I%20could%20stay%20on%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Rose%2C%20who%20is%20currently%20on%20disability.%20(For%20privacy%20reasons%2C%20she%20requested%20anonymity.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWithin%20days%20of%20starting%20the%20drugs%2C%20which%20she%20injected%20into%20her%20abdomen%2C%20she%20noticed%20a%20shift.%20She%20needed%20less%20insulin%2C%20and%20sometimes%20didn't%20any.%20But%20more%20importantly%2C%20she%20no%20longer%20spent%20hours%20ruminating%20on%20food%20and%20weight.%20And%20her%20hunger%20disappeared.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20actually%20freaked%20me%20out%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20wasn't%20intentionally%20restricting%2C%20but%20I%20had%20to%20force%20myself%20to%20remember%20to%20eat.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHer%20daily%20caloric%20intake%20plummeted%20to%20about%20850%20calories%20and%20then%20350%2C%20which%20she%20tracked%20with%20MyFitnessPal.%20She%20did%20an%20hour%20of%20cardio%20every%20day%20and%20regularly%20took%20laxatives%20and%20diuretics%2C%20all%20of%20which%20she%20hid%20from%20her%20team.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%2C%20of%20course%2C%20she%3Cem%3E%20liked%3C%2Fem%3E%20the%20weight%20loss.%20She%20couldn't%20help%20herself.%20As%20she%20put%20it%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20know%20I'm%20not%20taking%20it%20for%20the%20right%20reasons%2C%20but%20I%20still%20feel%20that%20I%20need%20to.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20a%20recent%20report%20in%20Annals%20of%20Internal%20Medicine%2C%20in%202022%20and%202023%20about%2024%2C500%20emergency%20room%20visits%20were%20linked%20to%20semaglutide%2C%20Ozempic's%20active%20ingredient%2C%20primarily%20due%20to%20severe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fozempic-stomach-paralysis-woman-says-weight-loss-drug-made-life-hell-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Egastrointestinal%20side%20effects%3C%2Fa%3E%20like%20nausea%2C%20vomiting%2C%20and%20abdominal%20pain.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202023%2C%20a%20Louisiana%20woman%20sued%20Novo%20Nordisk%20and%20Eli%20Lilly%2C%20the%20makers%20of%20Ozempic%20and%20Mounjaro%2C%20for%20not%20disclosing%20the%20risk%20of%20serious%20gastrointestinal%20issues%20caused%20by%20the%20drugs.%20(The%20case%20is%20still%20pending.)%20As%20of%20May%201%2C%20there%20have%20been%201%2C809%20lawsuits%20pending%20against%20the%20makers%20of%20GLP-1%20drugs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlmost%20everyone%20who%20stops%20taking%20the%20medications%20regains%20about%20two-thirds%20or%20more%20of%20the%20weight%20they%20lost%20on%20it%20%E2%80%94%20a%20widely%20accepted%20statistic%20that%20can%20make%20it%20hard%20for%20someone%20with%20an%20eating%20disorder%20to%20quit%20the%20drugs.%20But%20there%20are%20no%20studies%20on%20the%20long-term%20impacts%20of%20these%20drugs%20on%20health.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Joel%20Jahraus%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6881106f85e81483682e89ca%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDr.%20Joel%20Jahraus%2C%20vice%20president%20of%20medical%20services%20at%20eating%20disorder%20treatment%20provider%20Monte%20Nido%2C%20has%20seen%20a%20sharp%20increase%20in%20patients%20on%20GLP-1%20medications%20when%20they%20enter%20treatment.%3Cp%3ERodolfo%20Benitez%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20our%20population%2C%20people%20take%20it%20to%20a%20new%20level%2C%26quot%3B%20Jahraus%20said.%20%26quot%3BThey%20don't%20understand%20the%20risks%20involved.%20What%20are%20you%20going%20to%20do%20when%20you%20stop%20taking%20the%20medication%20for%20whatever%20reason%2C%20and%20you%20gain%20back%20two%20thirds%20of%20the%20weight%20you%20lost%3F%20To%20an%20eating%20disorder%20patient%2C%20that's%20a%20disaster.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELabels%20for%20Wegovy%20and%20Zepbound%20warn%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmounjaro-vs-ozempic-side-effects-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eside%20effects%3C%2Fa%3E%20like%20nausea%20and%20vomiting%2C%20but%20they%20say%20nothing%20about%20eating%20disorders%2C%20which%20affect%20nearly%201%20in%2010%20people%20in%20the%20United%20States%2C%20according%20to%20the%20National%20Association%20of%20Anorexia%20Nervosa%20and%20Associated%20Disorders.%20Anorexia%20nervosa%20has%20the%20highest%20mortality%20rate%20of%20any%20mental%20illness.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2247720dbd-3283-429e-878b-6376b862e8ec%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EDoctors%20fail%20to%20recognize%20eating%20disorders%20in%20people%20in%20larger%20bodies%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20issue%20is%20that%20many%20doctors%20aren't%20properly%20trained%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frising-rate-teens-hospitalized-by-eating-disorders-in-the-pandemic-2021-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eeating%20disorder%20treatment%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BPeople%20are%20often%20surprised%20to%20learn%20that%20routine%20screening%20for%20eating%20disorders%20risk%20does%20not%20occur%20in%20many%20medical%20settings%2C%20including%20those%20where%20GLP-1%20drugs%20are%20prescribed%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Dr.%20Doreen%20Marshall%2C%20CEO%20of%20the%20National%20Eating%20Disorders%20Association%20(NEDA).%20Many%20general%20medical%20practitioners%20receive%20limited%20or%20no%20training%20or%20education%20on%20eating%20disorders.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20especially%20true%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20patients%20in%20larger%20bodies%2C%20who%20might%20suffer%20from%20BED%20or%20atypical%20anorexia.%20Many%20doctors%20see%20a%20heavier%20patient%20and%20assume%20they%20simply%20need%20to%20lose%20weight%2C%20but%20that's%20not%20always%20true.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20prescribing%20for%20higher-weight%20people%20what%20we%20diagnose%20as%20eating%20disorders%20in%20thin%20people%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Deb%20Burgard%2C%20a%20psychologist%20and%20eating%20disorders%20specialist%2C%20and%20one%20of%20the%20founders%20of%20the%20Health%20at%20Every%20Size%20framework%20of%20care.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20breathless%20hype%20about%20a%20drug%20that%20aims%20to%20starve%20people%20is%20that%20it%20starves%20people%20seemingly%20without%20a%20protest%20from%20the%20starving%20body%2C%26quot%3B%20Burgard%20added.%20%26quot%3BFrom%20our%20bodies'%20point%20of%20view%2C%20starvation%20is%20a%20disaster%2C%20no%20matter%20the%20source.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%228192%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Chevesse%20Turner%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6881268085e81483682e8c30%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225464%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ETurner%20is%20sticking%20with%20Mounjaro%20to%20control%20her%20diabetes%2C%20but%20she%20says%20the%20drug%20has%20impacted%20her%20recovery%20strategy.%3Cp%3EAlyssa%20Schukar%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f8a51694-8315-4068-8dab-9d9ad2475ccd%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20do%20you%20stop%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20ideal%20world%2C%20Chevese%20Turner%20would%20eliminate%20Mounjaro%2C%20but%20the%20world%20doesn't%20bend%20to%20our%20whims.%20Her%20diabetes%20is%20under%20control%2C%20and%20that's%20important.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20she%20remains%20vigilant%20so%20she%20doesn't%20fall%20back%20into%20her%20old%20habits.%20She%20began%20setting%20a%20timer%20to%20remember%20when%20to%20eat%2C%20which%20she%20had%20done%20in%20the%20early%20stages%20of%20her%20recovery.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20had%20worked%20so%20hard%20for%20a%20long%20time%20to%20become%20an%20intuitive%20eater%20and%20my%20whole%20self%20has%20changed%20because%20I'm%20in%20recovery%20and%20I%20eat%20intuitively%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20just%20a%20totally%20different%20relationship%20with%20food%20and%20body.%20So%20I%20had%20to%20start%20going%20back%20to%20the%20very%20beginning%20of%20what%20I%20did%20in%20my%20recovery%2C%20and%20that%20was%20set%20timers%20to%20remember%20to%20eat.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20for%20Rose%2C%20she%20has%20lost%20about%2045%20pounds%20since%20starting%20Ozempic.%20After%20her%20insurance%20stopped%20covering%20it%2C%20she%20began%20paying%20%241%2C000%20a%20month%20out%20of%20pocket%20for%20a%20similar%20drug%2C%20Rybelsus%2C%20that%20a%20family%20member%20%E2%80%94%20believing%20she%20wanted%20it%20for%20her%20diabetes%20%E2%80%94%20helped%20her%20procure.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20would%20be%20devastated%20if%20they%20knew%20why%20I'm%20really%20taking%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20She%20has%20had%20regular%20appointments%20with%20her%20endocrinologist%2C%20but%20never%20discussed%20her%20GLP-1%20use.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20mid%20May%2C%20she%20ran%20out%20of%20Rybelsus%20and%20didn't%20refill%20it%3B%20it%20was%20too%20expensive.%20Around%20this%20same%20time%20she%20landed%20in%20the%20hospital%20with%20low%20potassium%2C%20which%20doctors%20blamed%20on%20her%20overuse%20of%20diuretics.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20she%20had%20her%20way%2C%20she'd%20go%20back%20on%20Ozempic%20to%20lose%20another%2045%20pounds.%20She's%20thinking%20about%20buying%20some%20online%2C%20which%20won't%20require%20a%20doctor's%20prescription.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%2C%20of%20course%2C%20is%20dangerous%20in%20its%20own%20right%2C%20as%20unregulated%20or%20unlicensed%20vendors%20have%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fscientist-cheaper-ozempic-sold-online-contains-dangerous-ingredients-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eselling%20fake%20Ozempic%20online%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20in%20medical%20spas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20June%202024%2C%20the%20World%20Health%20Organization%20warned%20about%20falsified%20batches%20of%20Ozempic%3B%20the%20National%20Association%20of%20Boards%20of%20Pharmacy%20identified%20thousands%20of%20websites%20illegally%20selling%20fraudulent%20weight-loss%20drugs.%20Worldwide%2C%2042%20people%20were%20hospitalized%20after%20taking%20fake%20injections%2C%20according%20to%20the%20FDA's%20Adverse%20Event%20Reporting%20System.%20Some%20people%20died.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERose%20knows%20she's%20playing%20with%20fire.%20Still%2C%20she%20isn't%20ready%20to%20give%20up%20the%20drug.%20%26quot%3BI%20feel%20like%20I'm%20doing%20better%20than%20I%20have%20in%20a%20while%2C%20but%20the%20thoughts%20of%20wanting%20to%20lose%20weight%20or%20take%20Ozempic%20don't%20ever%20go%20away.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fozempic-driving-a-new-eating-disorder