m-memberships-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esubscription%20economy%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20exploded%20in%20recent%20years%2C%20by%20one%20estimate%20growing%20by%20over%20400%25%20over%20the%20past%20decade.%20Companies%20love%20the%20idea%20of%20recurring%20revenue%20and%20sticky%20customer%20contracts%20that%20require%20some%20effort%20to%20escape.%20Given%20the%20allure%2C%20it's%20no%20surprise%20that%20subscription%20revenue%20is%20expected%20to%20reach%20%241.5%20trillion%20this%20year.%20Companies%20have%20developed%20a%20slew%20of%20ways%20to%20get%20us%20on%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerica-subscriptions-nightmare-recurring-payments-cancellation-company-tricks-trap-customers-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erecurring-charge%20hook%3C%2Fa%3E.%20One%20of%20the%20most%20popular%20methods%20of%20customer%20acquisition%20is%20free%20trials%2C%20which%20operate%20on%20the%20idea%20that%20a%20little%20taste%20of%20a%20service%20will%20persuade%20people%20to%20sign%20up%20fully%2C%20or%20maybe%20they'll%20just%20forget%20about%20it%20and%20keep%20paying%20anyway.%20And%20once%20people%20are%20hooked%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fftc-blocks-subscription-trap-click-to-cancel-ftc-rule-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Esome%20companies%3C%2Fa%3E%20make%20it%20harder%20than%20it%20should%20be%20to%20cancel.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20do%20feel%20like%20you%20have%20to%20have%20your%20wits%20about%20you%2C%20I%20think%2C%20in%20the%20world%20of%20subscriptions%20as%20a%20consumer%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Robbie%20Kellman%20Baxter%2C%20a%20consultant%20for%20subscription-based%20companies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20takeoff%20of%20hard-to-get-out-of%20subscriptions%20has%20been%20accompanied%20by%20a%20takeoff%20of%20crafty%20consumers%20finding%20ways%20to%20wiggle%20free%20of%20them.%20Shrewd%20customers%20are%20constantly%20starting%20and%20stopping%20new%20free%20and%20discounted%20subscriptions%20as%20a%20way%20to%20beat%20the%20Man.%20It%20takes%20a%20bit%20of%20work%2C%20but%20given%20companies'%20proclivity%20to%20keep%20people%20trapped%20in%20agreements%2C%20some%20people%20turn%20around%20and%20think%2C%20%26quot%3BWell%2C%20two%20can%20play%20at%20that%20game.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BConsumers%20are%20way%20more%20savvy%20about%20subscription%20free%20trials%20and%20deep%20discounts%20and%20are%20gaming%20the%20system%20more%20and%20more%2C%20to%20the%20point%20that%20it's%20become%20an%20issue%20for%20many%20subscription%20businesses%2C%26quot%3B%20Baxter%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20subscriptions%2C%20it's%20turned%20into%20an%20us-versus-them%20situation.%20%3Cem%3EThey%3C%2Fem%3E%20are%20hoping%20we%20won't%20have%20the%20wherewithal%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhollywood-streamers-oppose-ftc-proposal-regulation-click-to-cancel-subscription-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eclick%20(a%20few%20times)%20to%20cancel%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%3Cem%3EWe%3C%2Fem%3E%20are%20hoping%20those%20multiple%20calendar%20reminders%20to%20log%20into%20the%20random%20email%20we%20created%20last%20month%20and%20QUIT%20PEACOCK%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20trial%20will%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fbeauty%2Fclasspass-free-trial%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Elitany%20of%20tactics%3C%2Fa%3E%20people%20employ%20to%20try%20to%20game%20the%20free%20trials%20system%20ranges%20from%20elementary%20to%20borderline%20obsessive.%20People%20create%20new%20email%20accounts%20or%20get%20a%20friend%20or%20family%20member%20to%20chip%20in%20theirs.%20They%20set%20up%20reminders%20for%20themselves%20to%20quit%20before%20they%20have%20to%20cough%20up%20cash%2C%20an%20imperfect%20system%20at%20best.%20A%20friend%20of%20mine%20recently%20confessed%20he%20unlocks%20one%20of%20his%20credit%20cards%20only%20when%20he%20signs%20up%20for%20a%20subscription%20or%20books%20a%20restaurant%20reservation%20with%20a%20cancellation%20fee.%20He%20immediately%20locks%20it%20again%2C%20so%20if%20another%20charge%20comes%20in%2C%20it%20doesn't%20go%20through.%20He%20calls%20it%20his%20%26quot%3Bf-you%20card.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStephen%20Carlson%2C%20a%20designer%20in%20New%20York%2C%20finds%20himself%20on%20the%20more%20sophisticated%20end%20of%20the%20shenanigans%20spectrum.%20He%20sets%20up%20payments%20using%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2FPrivacy.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPrivacy.com%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20allows%20users%20to%20create%20temporary%2C%20anonymous%20card%20numbers%20connected%20to%20their%20bank%20account%20and%20set%20charge%20limits%20and%20expiration%20dates.%20So%2C%20he'll%20open%20an%20account%2C%20assign%20a%20dummy%20card%20to%20it%2C%20and%20then%20make%20it%20so%20the%20card%20expires%20right%20after%20the%20trial%20ends.%20The%20alert%20that%20the%20payment%20has%20been%20declined%20serves%20as%20a%20reminder%20that%20he%20opened%20the%20account%20in%20the%20first%20place%2C%20and%20he%20can%20decide%20from%20there%20whether%20to%20pay%20it%20or%20let%20it%20lapse.%20Privacy's%20dashboard%20also%20lets%20him%20track%20which%20cards%20he%20has%20open%20and%20what%20subscriptions%20they're%20assigned%20to%2C%20so%20he%20can%20monitor%20whether%20charges%20go%20up%20and%20see%20what%20he's%20signed%20up%20for.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20goal%20is%20to%20just%20not%20sign%20up%20for%20things%20and%20then%20forget%20about%20them%20while%20still%20paying%20for%20them%2C%20which%20is%20what%20I%20think%20subscription%20companies%20plan%20on%2C%26quot%3B%20Carlson%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDevin%20Boudreaux%2C%20a%20digital%20marketer%20in%20Idaho%2C%20waits%20for%20shows%20and%20movies%20he'd%20like%20to%20watch%20to%20stack%20up%20on%20different%20streaming%20services%20so%20he%20can%20sign%20up%2C%20binge%2C%20and%20quit.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbest-shows-streaming-on-apple-tv%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EApple%20TV%2B%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20specifically%2C%20is%20a%20good%20target%20for%20this%2C%20because%20they%20%26quot%3Bdon't%20necessarily%20ramp%20up%20a%20lot%20of%20content%20frequently%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20He%20just%20cycles%20through%20different%20emails%2C%20which%20are%20easy%20enough%20to%20create%2C%20and%20it's%20not%20like%20delivery%20platforms%20or%20media%20companies%20seem%20to%20closely%20track%20IP%20addresses%20or%20even%20physical%20addresses.%20%26quot%3BI%20feel%20like%20it's%20realistically%20not%20necessarily%20saving%20that%20much%20money%2C%20but%20it's%20like%2C%20oh%2C%20this%20is%20really%20easy%2C%20it%20takes%20two%20seconds%2C%20more%20or%20less%2C%20and%20I%20do%20think%20that%20little%20things%20do%20add%20up%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKaitlin%20Aviles-Castillo%2C%20a%20product%20marketer%20in%20Connecticut%2C%20tells%20me%20she%20views%20free%20trials%20on%20food%20delivery%20and%20workout%20passes%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bsweet%20treat%26quot%3B%20she%20rewards%20herself%20with%20from%20time%20to%20time.%20Given%20the%20increasing%20price%20for%20many%20of%20these%20services%2C%20she%20doesn't%20feel%20like%20she%20can%20stay%20attached%20over%20the%20long%20run%2C%20so%20she%20dips%20in%20and%20out%20as%20needed.%20Plus%2C%20companies%20often%20give%20newbies%20better%20deals%20than%20their%20longtime%20customers%2C%20making%20new%20sign-ups%20more%20valuable.%20Ashley%20Swett%2C%20a%20California%20account%20executive%20who%20has%20a%20habit%20of%20signing%20up%20for%20FuboTV%20trials%20to%20catch%20college%20football%20games%2C%20echoes%20the%20point%20on%20price.%20%26quot%3BSubscriptions%20have%20gotten%20so%20pricey%20these%20days%2C%20and%20there's%20so%20many%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20my%20coworkers%2C%20a%20self-described%20%26quot%3Bfiend%20for%20a%20deal%26quot%3B%20who's%20constantly%20scanning%20Facebook%20and%20Telegram%20groups%20for%20discounts%2C%20tells%20me%20that%20if%20I%20just%20move%20the%20dot%20around%20in%20my%20Gmail%20address%2C%20it'll%20still%20show%20up%20in%20my%20inbox%2C%20but%20a%20subscription%20company%20will%20read%20it%20as%20a%20totally%20new%20email.%20%26quot%3BI%20don't%20have%20any%20ethical%20qualms%20with%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20%26quot%3BI%20get%20what%20they're%20trying%20to%20do.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPlenty%20of%20people%20feel%20just%20fine%20engaging%20in%20some%20level%20of%20strategy%20around%20subscriptions.%20In%20an%20online%20survey%20conducted%20in%20May%202024%20by%20The%20Harris%20Poll%20on%20behalf%20of%20Zuora%2C%20a%20software%20company%20focused%20on%20subscription%20services%2C%2036%25%20of%20US%20adults%20said%20they'd%20canceled%20and%20rejoined%20the%20same%20service%20within%20a%20year%2C%20and%2057%25%20said%20they'd%20subscribed%20to%20a%20streaming%20service%20in%20order%20to%20watch%20a%20specific%20series%20or%20event%20and%20then%20canceled.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EFree%20trials%20%E2%80%94%20when%20done%20right%20%E2%80%94%20can%20be%20a%20win-win.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EConsumers%20get%20to%20experience%20something%20they%20were%20on%20the%20fence%20about%20and%20decide%20whether%20it's%20worth%20paying%20for.%20If%20they%20enjoy%20it%20and%20wind%20up%20sticking%20around%2C%20the%20seller%20gets%20the%20bang%20for%20the%20buck%20they%20lost%20by%20temporarily%20giving%20the%20thing%20away%20for%20free.%20But%20trials%20play%20into%20our%20psychology%20in%20other%2C%20less%20mutually%20beneficial%20ways.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENeale%20Mahoney%2C%20a%20Stanford%20economist%20who's%20studied%20subscriptions%2C%20explains%20that%20free%20trials%20take%20advantage%20of%20what%20behavioral%20economists%20call%20myopia%20or%20hyperbolic%20discounting%2C%20which%20is%20basically%20a%20nearsightedness%20on%20the%20part%20of%20consumers.%20We%20focus%20on%20the%20five%20free%20meals%20offered%20by%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fkitchen%2Fbest-meal-kit-delivery-service%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emeal%20kit%3C%2Fa%3E%20service%2C%20or%20the%20teaser%20rate%20on%20the%20credit%20card%20offer%2C%20and%20we%20view%20the%20charges%20that%20might%20come%20next%20as%20a%20later%20problem.%20They%20also%20leverage%20inertia.%20Many%20subscriptions%20are%20easy%20to%20get%20into%20and%20hard%20to%20get%20out%20of%2C%20hence%20the%20Federal%20Trade%20Commission's%20recently%20blocked%20attempt%20to%20compel%20companies%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fftc-blocks-subscription-trap-click-to-cancel-ftc-rule-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emake%20canceling%20easier%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Companies%20are%20constantly%20figuring%20out%20ways%20to%20get%20people%20to%20sign%20up%20and%20keep%20them%20from%20leaving.%20Just%20look%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-project-iliad-juiciest-highlights-ftc-prime-lawsuit-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAmazon's%20Project%20Iliad%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20was%20meant%20to%20make%20it%20hard%20for%20consumers%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-project-iliad-made-cancel-prime-membership-harer-leaked-data-2022-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecancel%20Prime%20memberships%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Mahoney%20says%20companies%20are%20constantly%20testing%20ways%20to%20keep%20people%20subscribed%20%E2%80%94%20how%20to%20convince%20them%20to%20sign%20up%2C%20keep%20them%20from%20quitting%2C%20and%20identify%20price%20points%20that%20will%20keep%20them%20hooked%2C%20including%20extra-low%20offers%20if%20they%20try%20to%20leave.%20The%20investment%20in%20constantly%20testing%20out%20new%20methods%20of%20retention%20is%20worth%20it%2C%20he%20says%2C%20because%20%26quot%3Bthey%20can%20collect%20more%20money%20than%20it%20costs%20them.%26quot%3B%20The%20subscription%20inertia%20is%20so%20strong%20that%20companies%20such%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbanking%2Frocket-money-app-review%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERocket%20Money%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20making%20money%20helping%20people%20to%20track%20and%20cancel%20their%20subscriptions%20(the%20service%20is%20a%20subscription%2C%20of%20course).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFree%20trials%20are%20a%20tempting%20type%20of%20%26quot%3Bnegative%20option%26quot%3B%20business%20practice%2C%20in%20which%20companies%20interpret%20a%20customer's%20lack%20of%20action%20on%20a%20subscription%20as%20consent%20to%20keep%20billing.%20In%20some%20areas%2C%20they%20make%20sense%20%E2%80%94%20I%20don't%20want%20to%20have%20to%20tell%20T-Mobile%20I%20still%20want%20to%20use%20my%20cellphone%20every%20month.%20But%20they%20can%20also%20be%20sneaky%20and%20lull%20people%20into%20paying%20for%20stuff%20much%20longer%20than%20they'd%20intended.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsiepr.stanford.edu%2Fpublications%2Fworking-paper%2Fselling-subscriptions%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOne%20research%20paper%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20Mahoney%20coauthored%20found%20that%20adding%20some%20level%20of%20friction%20to%20the%20subscription%20cancellation%20process%20raised%20revenues%20for%20companies%20by%2014%25%20to%20200%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCompanies%20don't%20need%20most%20people%20to%20forget%20to%20cancel%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Ayelet%20Fishbach%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20behavioral%20science%20and%20marketing%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Chicago.%20%26quot%3BJust%20a%20few%20is%20enough.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EA%20lot%20of%20people%20have%20at%20least%20one%20subscription%20cancellation%20nightmare%20story.%20I've%20got%20a%20bunch.%20A%20few%20months%20into%20the%20pandemic%2C%20my%20gym%20told%20me%20I%20couldn't%20quit%20my%20membership%20unless%20I%20came%20in%20person%20or%20sent%20them%20a%20certified%20letter%20in%20the%20mail%20saying%20I%20wanted%20out.%20Regular%20mail%2C%20apparently%2C%20didn't%20cut%20it.%20Earlier%20this%20year%2C%20I%20spent%20months%20calling%20a%20small%20publication%20trying%20to%20cancel%20a%20subscription%20I%20didn't%20even%20remember%20signing%20up%20for%2C%20and%20I%20eventually%20had%20to%20call%20my%20credit%20card%20company%20to%20block%20them%20from%20charging%20me.%20Sometimes%2C%20I've%20played%20the%20system%2C%20too.%20Recently%2C%20I%20got%20a%20%24100%20voucher%20in%20the%20mail%20to%20order%20a%20case%20of%20wine.%20I%20did%20a%20little%20online%20research%20and%20discovered%20the%20catch%20was%20that%20if%20I%20ordered%20the%20wine%2C%20the%20company%20would%20sign%20me%20up%20to%20be%20a%20monthly%20donor%20to%20its%20winemakers%2C%20which%20was%20not%20very%20obvious%20in%20its%20original%20order.%20Since%20they%20were%20trying%20to%20trick%20me%2C%20I%20decided%20to%20trick%20them%20back%20%E2%80%94%20once%20the%20wine%20arrived%2C%20I%20immediately%20canceled%20my%20membership.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOur%20consumer%20economy%20has%20trained%20us%20to%20act%20this%20way.%20Consumers%20are%20on%20the%20lookout%20for%20how%20companies%20are%20going%20to%20try%20to%20squeeze%20the%20most%20money%20out%20of%20them%2C%20and%20so%20they're%20engaging%20in%20their%20own%20ruses%20in%20turn.%20On%20free%20trials%2C%20some%20of%20the%20pros%20on%20the%20subscriptions%20side%20even%20acknowledge%20that%20you%20really%20can't%20blame%20consumers%20for%20acting%20like%20this.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmy%20Konary%2C%20who%20heads%20a%20think%20tank%20at%20Zuora%2C%20says%20free%20trial%20subscriptions%20should%20serve%20as%20%26quot%3Bfeedback%26quot%3B%20for%20businesses%20that%20the%20product%20or%20service%20they're%20trying%20to%20sell%20isn't%20worth%20the%20price%20they're%20charging%20in%20a%20prospective%20customer's%20mind.%20%26quot%3BThere%20should%20not%20be%20any%20trickery%20on%20any%20side%2C%20and%20no%20one%20should%20be%20feeling%20guilty%20about%20anything%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20%26quot%3BAny%20type%20of%20a%20merchant-consumer%20relationship%20is%20an%20exchange%20of%20fair%20value.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20value%20proposition%20is%20not%20compelling%2C%26quot%3B%20Baxter%20says.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20I%20think%20a%20lot%20of%20organizations%20do%20a%20free%20trial%20because%20nobody's%20buying%2C%20nobody's%20signing%20up.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20doesn't%20mean%20scheming%20around%20free%20trials%20is%20a%20victimless%20crime.%20Mahoney%20says%20there's%20a%20%26quot%3Breverse%20Robin%20Hood%26quot%3B%20element%20to%20the%20issue%2C%20and%20not%20the%20type%20you%20may%20think.%20The%20people%20who%20have%20the%20time%20and%20energy%20to%20game%20free%20trial%20systems%20are%20most%20likely%20more%20sophisticated%20and%20higher-income%20than%20the%20people%20who%20do%20not.%20That%20may%20lead%20companies%20to%20increase%20their%20subscription%20costs%20and%20make%20quitting%20a%20little%20more%20difficult%2C%20and%20it%20ultimately%20hurts%20less%20sophisticated%2C%20lower-income%20people%20who%20aren't%20playing%20any%20games.%20It%20also%20hurts%20the%20more%20sophisticated%20people%20who%20are%20wasting%20all%20this%20time%20to%20squeeze%20an%20extra%20%245%20out%20of%20Hulu.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSo%20many%20things%20about%20that%20economy%20are%20just%20problematic%2C%26quot%3B%20Mahoney%20says.%20%26quot%3BYou%20don't%20want%20to%20hurt%20unsophisticated%20low-income%20people%2C%20and%20you%20don't%20want%20a%20bunch%20of%20people%20just%20spending%20their%20time%20playing%20games.%20It's%20not%20productive.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Femily-stewart%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EEmily%20Stewart%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20senior%20correspondent%20at%20Business%20Insider%2C%20writing%20about%20business%20and%20the%20economy.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20ori