2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFortunately%20for%20Chinese%20exporters%2C%20external%20demand%20from%20other%20economies%20has%20helped%20offset%20much%20of%20the%20drag%20from%20the%20US%2C%26quot%3B%20wrote%20Lynn%20Song%2C%20ING's%20chief%20economist%20for%20Greater%20China%2C%20in%20a%20Wednesday%20note.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20May%2C%20China's%20shipments%20to%20the%20US%20plunged%20nearly%2035%25%20from%20a%20year%20ago%20following%20Trump's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-liberation-day-reciprocal-tariffs-speech-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E%26quot%3BLiberation%20Day%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20tariff%20announcements.%20But%20China's%20export%20machine%20still%20grew%20about%205%25%20in%20the%20same%20month%20because%20its%20fast-growing%20trade%20started%20to%20flow%20elsewhere.%20Shipments%20fell%2016%25%20in%20June%20despite%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-china-trade-deal-agreement-slash-trump-tariffs-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Etrade%20truce%3C%2Fa%3E%20between%20the%20two%20economic%20giants.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20first%20half%20of%20the%20year%2C%20China's%20exports%20to%20the%20world%20grew%205.9%25%20from%20a%20year%20earlier%2C%20defying%20expectations%20of%20a%20broad%20slowdown.%20Growth%20came%20from%20trade%20with%20Southeast%20Asia%2C%20the%20EU%2C%20Latin%20America%2C%20and%20India%2C%20according%20to%20a%20recent%20analysis%20from%20ING.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EING%20isn't%20the%20only%20one%20seeing%20the%20trend.%20In%20a%20Monday%20note%2C%20analysts%20at%20Goldman%20Sachs%20wrote%20that%20China's%20exports%20have%20been%20%26quot%3Bresilient%2C%26quot%3B%20in%20part%20thanks%20to%20trade%20rerouting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Goldman%20Sachs%20analysts%20wrote%20that%20part%20of%20China's%20export%20resilience%20stems%20from%20%26quot%3Bthe%20fluidity%20of%20goods%20trade%20and%20Chinese%20exporters'%20ability%20to%20reroute%20trade%20flows.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E