e%20bloc%20fell%20by%20just%205.2%25%20in%20the%20first%20half%20of%20the%20year%2C%20with%20declines%20led%20by%20Belgium%20and%20Germany.%20However%2C%20auto%20exports%20to%20Italy%20and%20Spain%20accelerated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20diversification%20is%20helping%20to%20offset%20steep%20declines%20in%20traditional%2C%20low-end%20categories%20like%20toys%2C%20furniture%2C%20and%20footwear%2C%20which%20have%20been%20hit%20hard%20by%20tariffs%20and%20are%20more%20easily%20replaced%20by%20alternative%20suppliers%2C%20Song%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnalysts%20expect%20China's%20growth%20to%20moderate%20in%20the%20second%20half%20of%20the%20year%2C%20particularly%20as%20the%20effects%20of%20front-loading%20to%20transshipment%20countries%20fade.%20However%2C%20exports%20will%20still%20be%20a%20key%20growth%20contributor%2C%20potentially%20helping%20the%20country%20reach%20its%20growth%20target%20of%20around%205%25%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSo%20long%20as%20global%20growth%20is%20steady%20and%20end-demand%20is%20healthy%2C%20Chinese%20exports%20are%20likely%20to%20continue%20to%20rise%20given%20their%20extreme%20competitiveness%20and%20the%20difficulties%20for%20bilateral%20tariffs%20to%20reduce%20overall%20trade%20flows%2C%26quot%3B%20wrote%20Goldman%20Sachs's%20analysts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-china-exports-economy-growth-despite-us-trump-trade-tariffs-2025-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1753339124000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68819c6ef748d8c055f62d33%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-china-exports-economy-growth-despite-us-trump-trade-tariffs-2025-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Over%20the%20first%20half%20of%202025%2C%20China's%20exports%20to%20the%20world%20grew%20nearly%206%25%20from%20a%20year%20earlier%2C%20defying%20expectations%20of%20a%20bro